{"title_page": "Passion Pictures", "text_new": "{{short description|Animation studio}}\n'''Passion Pictures''' is an animation production company established by [[Andrew Ruhemann]] in 1987. The company has studios in [[London]], [[Melbourne]], [[Paris]], [[Toronto]] and [[New York City]].\n\n==Film production==\nThe company's core business is in commercial and animation output, which includes work for [[Cartoon Network]], music videos for [[Gorillaz]], and the [[Compare the Market.com]] commercial campaign featuring [[Aleksandr Orlov (meerkat)]]. Passion Australia produced ''[[The Lost Thing]]'', directed by Andrew Ruhemann and [[Shaun Tan]], which won an [[Academy Award for Best Animated Short Film]] in 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2011|title=The 83rd Academy Awards {{!}} 2011|website=Oscars.org {{!}} Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences|language=en|access-date=2019-03-16}}</ref><ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=e90G8YxzUbI \"The Lost Thing\" winning Best Animated Short Film-Oscars on YouTube]</ref>\n\nThe department's first film, ''[[One Day in September]]'', won an [[Academy Award]] in 2000.<ref>{{Citation|title=One Day in September (1999)|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/one_day_in_september|language=en|access-date=2019-03-16}}</ref><ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s-HL7b3ae8E Documentary Winners: 2000 Oscars]</ref> They have since been involved in the 2013 Oscar-winning ''[[Searching for Sugar Man]]'' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2014/05/oscar-winning-searching-for-sugar-man-director-dead-at-36-26775/|title=Oscar-Winning 'Searching For Sugar Man' Director Dead at 36|last=Bernstein|first=Paula|last2=Bernstein|first2=Paula|date=2014-05-13|website=IndieWire|language=en|access-date=2019-03-16}}</ref> <ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hmYznlSk2Ig \"Searching for Sugar Man\" winning Best Documentary Feature-Oscars on YouTube]</ref>, 2015's ''[[Listen to Me Marlon]]'' <ref>[https://www.worldcat.org/title/listen-to-me-marlon/oclc/1076586836 Listen to me Marlon (DVD video, 2018)-WorldCat]</ref> and 2016's Oscar-nominated ''[[Pear Cider and Cigarettes]]''. <ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qZKs5VM5msc Official trailer on YouTube]</ref> <ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g4Fdmra44g0 \"Piper\" wins Best Animated Short Film-Oscars on YouTube]</ref>\nIn 2017, the company produced the [[Netflix]] docu-series ''[[Five Came Back (TV series)|Five Came Back]]'' based on the book by [[Mark Harris (journalist)|Mark Harris]].They also work on ''[[101 Dalmatian Street]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Exclusive: See the Trailer for Netflix's New Documentary About World War II and Hollywood|url=https://time.com/4677556/netflix-trailer-five-came-back/|website=Time|accessdate=February 28, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170228180839/http://time.com/4677556/netflix-trailer-five-came-back/|archive-date=2017-02-28|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.passion-pictures.com/}}\n* {{IMDb company|0572035}}\n* [https://www.screendaily.com/features/the-brit-50-passion-pictures/5133947.article The Brit 50 on Screen Daily]\n\n{{Animation industry in the United Kingdom}}\n\n[[Category:British animation studios]]\n[[Category:Film production companies of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 1987]]\n\n\n{{animation-studio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Animation studio}}\n'''Passion Pictures''' is an animation production company established by Andrew Ruhemann in 1987. The company has studios in [[London]], [[Melbourne]], [[Paris]], [[Toronto]] and [[New York City]].\n\n==Film production==\nThe company's core business is in commercial and animation output, which includes work for [[Cartoon Network]], music videos for [[Gorillaz]], and the [[Compare the Market.com]] commercial campaign featuring [[Aleksandr Orlov (meerkat)]]. Passion Australia produced ''[[The Lost Thing]]'', directed by Andrew Ruhemann and [[Shaun Tan]], which won an [[Academy Award for Best Animated Short Film]] in 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2011|title=The 83rd Academy Awards {{!}} 2011|website=Oscars.org {{!}} Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences|language=en|access-date=2019-03-16}}</ref><ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=e90G8YxzUbI \"The Lost Thing\" winning Best Animated Short Film-Oscars on YouTube]</ref>\n\nThe department's first film, ''[[One Day in September]]'', won an [[Academy Award]] in 2000.<ref>{{Citation|title=One Day in September (1999)|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/one_day_in_september|language=en|access-date=2019-03-16}}</ref><ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s-HL7b3ae8E Documentary Winners: 2000 Oscars]</ref> They have since been involved in the 2013 Oscar-winning ''[[Searching for Sugar Man]]'' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2014/05/oscar-winning-searching-for-sugar-man-director-dead-at-36-26775/|title=Oscar-Winning 'Searching For Sugar Man' Director Dead at 36|last=Bernstein|first=Paula|last2=Bernstein|first2=Paula|date=2014-05-13|website=IndieWire|language=en|access-date=2019-03-16}}</ref> <ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hmYznlSk2Ig \"Searching for Sugar Man\" winning Best Documentary Feature-Oscars on YouTube]</ref>, 2015's ''[[Listen to Me Marlon]]'' <ref>[https://www.worldcat.org/title/listen-to-me-marlon/oclc/1076586836 Listen to me Marlon (DVD video, 2018)-WorldCat]</ref> and 2016's Oscar-nominated ''[[Pear Cider and Cigarettes]]''. <ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qZKs5VM5msc Official trailer on YouTube]</ref> <ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g4Fdmra44g0 \"Piper\" wins Best Animated Short Film-Oscars on YouTube]</ref>\nIn 2017, the company produced the [[Netflix]] docu-series ''[[Five Came Back (TV series)|Five Came Back]]'' based on the book by [[Mark Harris (journalist)|Mark Harris]].They also work on ''[[101 Dalmatian Street]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Exclusive: See the Trailer for Netflix's New Documentary About World War II and Hollywood|url=https://time.com/4677556/netflix-trailer-five-came-back/|website=Time|accessdate=February 28, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170228180839/http://time.com/4677556/netflix-trailer-five-came-back/|archive-date=2017-02-28|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.passion-pictures.com/}}\n* {{IMDb company|0572035}}\n* [https://www.screendaily.com/features/the-brit-50-passion-pictures/5133947.article The Brit 50 on Screen Daily]\n\n{{Animation industry in the United Kingdom}}\n\n[[Category:British animation studios]]\n[[Category:Film production companies of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 1987]]\n\n\n{{animation-studio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Wavingdragon", "label": "safe", "comment": "Internal link for Andrew Ruhemann", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Passion_Pictures"}
